The paper deals with algorithmic graph theory and specifically focuses on the Maximum Independent Set problem on certain classes of graphs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the Exponential-Time Hypothesis (ETH) and provides time complexity bounds, indicating that it may also be relevant to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The paper also discusses the structure of graphs and their components, which suggests that it may be relevant to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with approximation algorithms, which may make it relevant to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
